 </div><div class="t m74a x66 h8 y126 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SUNDAY: Respect for &quot;Gray Hair&quot; </div><div class="t m573 x35 h8 y126 ff2 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(1 Pet. 5:5). </div><div class="t m74b x66 h8 y127 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">MONDAY: Honoring Our Parents </div><div class="t m568 x9f h8 y76b ff2 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Exod. 20:12). </div><div class="t m74c x66 h8 y128 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">TUESDAY: What About Obedience </div><div class="t mf2 x24 h8 y128 ff2 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Eph. 6:1-3, Col. 3:20). </div><div class="t m74d x66 h8 y129 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">WEDNESDAY: Parents and Children: Part 1. </div><div class="t m74e x66 h8 y12a ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">THURSDAY: Parents and Children: Part 2. </div><div class="t m74f x66 h7a y204 ff5 fse fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Memory </div><div class="t m750 xd8 h7a y204 ff9 fse fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Text</div><div class="t m751 x6d h79 y204 ff9 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">—</div><div class="t m304 xf3 h7a y204 ff9 fse fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Isaiah </div><div class="t m197 x15 h8 y12c ff2 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6:1, NRSV. </div><div class="t m703 x66 h7a y5d9 ff5 fse fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sabbath Gem: This </div><div class="t m344 xd3 h8 y12d ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">week we&apos;ll take a look at how children, or even </div><div class="t m14c x66 h8 y235 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">how adults, should relate not only to their parents but to those who are </div><div class="t m38 x66 h8 y12f ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">older, in general. Because, in almost all cases, no matter who we are or </div><div class="t m190 x66 h8 y130 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">how old we are, we come in contact with those who are even older. </div><div class="t m752 x68 h15 y38 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lessons for the Visually Impaired </div><div class="t m5d0 x82 h46 y1b6 ff6 fs24 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The regular Adult Sabbath School </div><div class="t m684 x68 h46 y55c ff6 fs24 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Bible Study Guide is available free each month in braille and on audiocass